item.title: Maroon 5 - "Goodnight Goodnight [Kno Remix]" (12.05.08)
item.description:
Popular rock act Maroon 5 will release a remix disc entitled Call And Response on December 9th 2008, albeit a Blue Schooler short of a masterpiece. Kno was hand-picked to rework one of Maroon 5’s previous tracks, and along with notable producers Just Blaze, ?uestlove, DJ Premier and others went about the task of re-working the vocals of lead singer Adam Levine (Kanye West’s "Heard Em’ Say" & Alicia Keys’ "Wild Horses") and studio stem files for a track of their choosing.
Unfortunately, Kno’s contribution to the batch had to be left off of the final tracklisting by A&M Records at the last minute due to a sample clearance issue, although there is still a chance the track will find an official home if the problems are worked out. Thanks to Brandon Phelps, Adam Levine & the band and everyone at Octone for the opportunity, hopefully this will lead to more great music in the future // www.QN5.com.

item.title: WQN5 PODTALK - Show #4 (02.14.08) - "My Funny Valentine"
item.description:
Tying in with the release of Baby Blue For Pink, QN5 Music presents: My Funny Valentine, an exclusive podcast created for URB.com for Valentines Day.

Featuring the QN5 collective sharing some of their most private love/sex/relationship experiences, no matter how embarrassing or explicit, this podcast also gives you a full version of Tonedeff’s new Domingo-produced scintillator, 'Close' from BBFP. If you haven’t picked up the EP yet, and need something for the drive home, this is exactly what the doctor ordered. And the best part is it's 100% FREE.

Podcast Tracklisting:
1. Introduction w/ Dick Brickhouse
2. Natti - Guest In The Trousers
3. CunninLynguists - Wonderful (f/ Devin The Dude) - [Produced By Kno]
4. PackFM - One Thing In Common
5. Tonedeff & PackFM - Love Q&A
6. Tonedeff - Close [Produced By Domingo]
7. Muddy Teacup (Skit)
8. Deacon The Villain - Pickle Juice
9. Substantial - Q.T. (Quality Time) - [Produced By Final]
10. Dick Brickhouse (Outtro)
11. Substantial - Kiss On The Cheek

For More Info: QN5.com

item.description: The second installment of The Late Pass w/ Domingo brings an all new set of classic-yet-forgotten bangers. This episode also includes the winning remix of "Passin Me By" by RahSoul (Crate Thieves Productions). The remix fun continues as we've included an ultra-rare acapella of "Crooklyn Dodgers". The Late Pass serves as a) a guided tour of essential old school hip-hop classics & breaks for newbies b) production tips and tricks and c) RARE acapellas and remix contests only Domingo can bring you! The New Hip-Hop continues to build from the blocks of tradition and Domingo has The Late Pass for all the latecomers! For More Information, visit: http://www.qn5.com/radio
